volume.name: Joe Psycho & Moo Frog Halloween Special

description: A strange spell is exploding out of control in Castle Grayskull! Only one person can save the lives of everyone in Eternia, and that person is? Orko?!
name: Orko

description: Meet Alien Legion: home to every scumbag the universe saw fit to dump in a uniform! And then there's Force Nomad - hard-bitten warriors, loyal to each other, but not to those that send them to die in unmarked graves!
name: TPB

description: They are the Dregs; the lost and the forsaken; loyal only to each other. Lost for 15 years in a black hole, Force Nomad return to combat. However, being used as pawns for the idle rich is something they won't stand for - as their paymasters are about to find out! Volume 2 in a major new Titan series of this popular classic comic, this volume collects Alien Legion: Tenants of Hell #1 & #2 and Alien Legion: Grimrod, along with new cover artwork by Alan Davis and an introduction by writer Chuck Dixon! Plus, previously- unseen development sketches, and character biographies featuring amazing artwork by Larry Stroman!
name: TPB

description: A dark, cynical thriller set in urban Britain. When Charlie moves into his new flat, he meets a colorful array of new characters, including a dominatrix and a skinhead yabo, witnesses a murder, and finds himself on the run from assassins and fixers sent by the highest levels of government. Shades of Howard Chaykin's Black Kiss and the hardboiled style of 100 Bullets, all with a very British (as in Lock Stock and Two Smoking Barrels British) accent.
name: HC

description: Stories on Jack Kirby's New Gods, Amethyst. Interview with Fred Hembeck.
New Gods History part 2, interview with the creators of Coyote.
Interview with John Byrne, focusing on Alpha Flight.
An inside look at Marvel's Crystar, the early days of the Hulk, Challengers of the Unknown.
DNAgents preview, the many women of Daredevil's life.
Stories and interviews about Ronin and Star Hawks.
Special preview of Edge Of Chaos, history of Nick Fury and forgotten heroes of the 1940s
An interview with the creators of Thriller. An index and review of DC's Imaginary Stories.
A look at the New Mutants, Green Arrow and Prince Namor.
